 a strong-coupling critical point in suspended graphene,\nsignifying either a quantum phase transition or a breakdown of the\nweak-coupling RG approach. We show that the latter is more likely by adapting\nDyson's argument for the breakdown of perturbative QED to the case of graphene.\nWe propose future experiments and theoretical directions to make further\nprogress on this important and difficult problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Jan 2014 21:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Feb 2014 18:33:11 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 20 Mar 2014 00:33:21 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 30 Jun 2014 16:40:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-01"}
